If you were using the /links endpoint to retrieve links/banners and links/text, please make the following adjustments –
https://publisherpro.flexoffers.com/DataFeeds/APIFrame#!/links/promotions
 
Instead of calling /links/text please update to the following /promotions?linkType=TextLinks 
https://api.flexoffers.com/promotions?linkType=TextLinks&page=1&pageSize=50
 
Instead of calling /links/banners please update to the following /promotions?linkType=Banners
https://api.flexoffers.com/promotions?linkType=Banners&page=1&pageSize=50
 
Or if you wish to query both links & banners please use /promotions?linkType=All
https://api.flexoffers.com/promotions?linkType=All&page=1&pageSize=50
 
To see full documentation for our /promotional endpoint please visit this page.
https://publisherpro.flexoffers.com/DataFeeds/APIDocumentation
 
You can also now take advantage of our /coupons API endpoint, any advertiser that makes coupon codes available will be present on that API result, you will now be able to see more accurate information with the correct Coupon Codes, Start Date, End Date and Coupon Restrictions if available.
https://publisherpro.flexoffers.com/DataFeeds/APIFrame#!/links/promotions_0
 
And lastly, we have made our Promotional Types available as well so you can query either our /promotions or /coupons API for things such as “General Promotion”, “Percentage Off”, “Free Shipping”.
 
If you call this endpoint it will retrieve all the list of PromotionTypes with their corresponding ID’s that will allow you to use on the /promotions and /coupons endpoint.
https://api.flexoffers.com/promotionTypes
 
Lastly, we updated our /advertisers API endpoint please note the following –
 
·         We have added an option to query by all our advertisers using the &ApplicationStatus=All 


·         We have made an adjustment to combine the &AllowsDeeplinking= and &Flexlinks= query parameters now you have to query them using &Deeplink/Flexlinks= and you will need to query them like this

http://api.flexoffers.com/advertisers?ProgamStatus=approved&ApplicationStatus=approved&Deeplink/Flexlinks=True&Page=1&pageSize=500

·         We have also added a parameter to search by advertisers who have Product Data Feeds available, you can query by using the query parameter &ProductAdvertiser=True

cards.desc:
Hope you are doing well.
 
Wanted to send out a note to let you and your team know that we have done some updates to our textlinks/banners and promotional API.
 
We have redesigned our whole Promotional/Coupon Feeds import and API and FTP, we are going to be importing more frequently throughout the day and the data is a lot more accurate.
 
In case you are using any of these following endpoints please take note -
 
If you were using the /links endpoint to retrieve links/banners and links/text, please make the following adjustments –
https://publisherpro.flexoffers.com/DataFeeds/APIFrame#!/links/promotions
 
Instead of calling /links/text please update to the following /promotions?linkType=TextLinks 
https://api.flexoffers.com/promotions?linkType=TextLinks&page=1&pageSize=50
 
Instead of calling /links/banners please update to the following /promotions?linkType=Banners
https://api.flexoffers.com/promotions?linkType=Banners&page=1&pageSize=50
 
Or if you wish to query both links & banners please use /promotions?linkType=All
https://api.flexoffers.com/promotions?linkType=All&page=1&pageSize=50
 
To see full documentation for our /promotional endpoint please visit this page.
https://publisherpro.flexoffers.com/DataFeeds/APIDocumentation
 
You can also now take advantage of our /coupons API endpoint, any advertiser that makes coupon codes available will be present on that API result, you will now be able to see more accurate information with the correct Coupon Codes, Start Date, End Date and Coupon Restrictions if available.
https://publisherpro.flexoffers.com/DataFeeds/APIFrame#!/links/promotions_0
 
And lastly, we have made our Promotional Types available as well so you can query either our /promotions or /coupons API for things such as “General Promotion”, “Percentage Off”, “Free Shipping”.
 
If you call this endpoint it will retrieve all the list of PromotionTypes with their corresponding ID’s that will allow you to use on the /promotions and /coupons endpoint.
https://api.flexoffers.com/promotionTypes
 
Lastly, we updated our /advertisers API endpoint please note the following –
 
·         We have added an option to query by all our advertisers using the &ApplicationStatus=All 


·         We have made an adjustment to combine the &AllowsDeeplinking= and &Flexlinks= query parameters now you have to query them using &Deeplink/Flexlinks= and you will need to query them like this

http://api.flexoffers.com/advertisers?ProgamStatus=approved&ApplicationStatus=approved&Deeplink/Flexlinks=True&Page=1&pageSize=500

·         We have also added a parameter to search by advertisers who have Product Data Feeds available, you can query by using the query parameter &ProductAdvertiser=True
